title: Monitor status of disk in Fujitsu Siemens ETERNUS DX storage systems
agents: SNMP
author: Lars Michelsen <lm@mathias-kettner.de>
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the reported status of all installed disks
 in storage systems from Fujitsu Siemens which support the
 FJDARY-E60.MIB like the ETERNUS DX60 and DX80.

item:
 The index of the device enclosure in the SNMP table. It is of type
 integer. The first module has an index of {0}.

inventory:
 The check supports automatic inventory. All available items which have
 a state other than {notavailable} (3) during the inventory run are added to the
 configuration. The {notavailable} state indicates that one disk is not installed.

[parameters]
expected_state (number): The expected state where the check reports {OK}.
 On all other states the check will report {CRITICAL}. Valid states are:
 {1}: available, {2}: broken, {3}: notavailable, {4}: notsupported, {5}: present,
 {6}: readying, {7}: recovering, {64}: partbroken, {65}: spare, {66}: formating,
 {67}: unformated, {68}: notexist, {69}: copying.
